The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Unitech in ally hunt
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Unitech in ally hunt
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	New Delhi, July 30: Unitech Ltd has appointed Swiss investment banker UBS to look for a foreign strategic partner for its telecom arm. Unitech will sell 26 per cent stake in its telecom arm to the foreign firm.         
	Unitech Wireless, which has a pan-India telecom licence, today said it would launch operations in the first quarter of next year.         
	We have appointed UBS for searching partners, while management consultant McKinsey has been hired to chalk out the overall telecom business plan, said Unitech managing director Sanjay Chandra.        
	Unitech, which has no previous experience in running a telecom business, is looking to tie up with foreign firms to use their technical expertise and financial strength, the company said.         
	Analyst estimate the total investment required for Unitechs telecom venture at Rs 20,000 crore over the next three years. Unitech Wireless, has also floated a request for proposal for telecom equipment, and five firms  ZTE, Huawei, Alcatel-Lucent, Nokia, Ericsson  have sent expressions of interest. The company will hire 500 professionals by September to manage the telecom business.        
	Profit soars        
	Unitech Ltd has reported a 15.6 per cent rise in consolidated net profit for the first quarter ended June 30 at Rs 423.31 crore compared with 365.67 crore in the year-ago period. The company hopes to maintain this growth momentum despite rising borrowing costs.                                                                                                                                      
